To install software in Linux, launch turtlebot3 gazebo simulator,  and MATLAB
To install a software  in linux
sudo dpkg -i  ./<filename>               filename is generally deb

To launch my_bot and turtlebot3
1) cd mybot_ws
2) source devel/setup.bash
3) roslaunch mybot_gazebo mybot_world.launch

For ROS turtlebot3 simulator,  type directly in terminal 
roslaunch turtlebot3_gazebo turtlebot3_empty_world.launch 
if it fails, source setup.bash as shown in step 2. Not necessarily same directory name.

To view ROS camera output in the terminal 
rosrun image_view image_view image:=/mybot/camera1/image_raw

To Launch MATLAB
1) cd /usr/local/MATLAB/2019b/bin
2) ./matlab
